When using React, the gridRef.current.api is not available until after the async creation of the Grid. If you want to do something when the grid is ready, please do it in onGridReady where the API is always available.

Alternatively, please reference the API as shown below:
useEffect(() => {
    if (gridRef.current.api) {
      console.log('gridRef', gridRef.current.api);
    }    
  }, [rowData]);

This behavior is happening because this is an inline-declared valueFormatter inside an AgGridColumn as shown below:
<AgGridColumn
            field="price"
            minWidth={120}
            valueFormatter={(params) => {
              return params.value
                .toString()
                .replace(/\B(?=(\d{3})+(?!\d))/g, ',');
            }}
          />

Each time the React render happens, this callback is another instance (as its in-line), and hence the grid sees a new callback, so it thinks the Column Definitions have changed. Because the grid thinks the Column Definitions have changed, it sets the new columns, which resets the column order.

You can address this in either of two ways:
1. Dont use an inline func for the callback. Demonstrated here:
https://plnkr.co/edit/1mW0XH4KwolTlIXu

2. Use JavaScript Col Defs. Demonstrated here:
https://plnkr.co/edit/mbovGvbQFQv30RGH

An example of a typed tooltip in the Grid is as follows:<br/>
<pre>
import React, {forwardRef, ForwardRefRenderFunction, useImperativeHandle} from 'react';
import {ITooltipParams} from "@ag-grid-community/core";
import {ITooltipReactComp} from "@ag-grid-community/react";

interface MyTooltipParams extends ITooltipParams {
    color?: string
}

const CustomTooltip: ForwardRefRenderFunction<ITooltipReactComp, MyTooltipParams> = (props, ref) => {
    const data = props.api!.getDisplayedRowAtIndex(props.rowIndex!)!.data;

    useImperativeHandle((ref), () => ({
        getReactContainerClasses() {
            return ['custom-tooltip'];
        },
    }));

    return (
        <div
            className="custom-tooltip"
            style={{backgroundColor: props.color || 'white'}}
        >
            <p>
                <span>{data.athlete}</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <span>Country: </span> {data.country}
            </p>
            <p>
                <span>Total: </span> {data.total}
            </p>
        </div>
    );
};

export default forwardRef(CustomTooltip);
</pre>

