This extra whitespace displayed under the collapsed master row is caused by the min-height placed on the grid. This is done so that messages such as 'no rows to display' can be displayed correctly in the body of the grid when there are no rows.

To override this minimum height, please remove the min-width styles by adding this style code:
      .ag-center-cols-container, .ag-center-cols-clipper {
        min-height: 0px !important;
      }

Once you apply this style removing the minimum height, note that there's no more extra space under the master row:
